article.headline: Sales fuels Sun with season-high 26 points
article.linkText: Sun burn Sparks for eighth straight victory
article.story:
LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Nykesha Sales scored a season-high 26 points
as the Connecticut Sun won their eighth straight game, beating the
Los Angeles Sparks 90-70 Monday night.

Katie Douglas added 18 points and Lindsay Whalen a season-best
16 for the Sun (8-1). Connecticut leads Indiana by two games in the
Eastern Conference of the WNBA.

Connecticut tied a season high with 39 rebounds and shot a
season-best 53 percent in its highest point output.

Chamique Holdsclaw had 23 points and Lisa Leslie 13 for the
Sparks (6-5), who fell 2½ games behind leader Sacramento in the
West.

Connecticut used an 18-4 surge to take a 22-10 lead with 10:14
left in the first half. Taj McWilliams-Franklin led the burst with
six points as the Sun made nine of 12 shots.

Los Angeles narrowed the deficit to 24-14. But another 18-4
surge gave the Sun a 42-18 lead with 4:36 left in the first half.
The Sparks scored only four points and made just one basket in a
span of 4:51.

Connecticut led by as many as 27 points in the second half.
